Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Comply and register with the sex offender registry for the length of probation plus 15 years;
3) Provide DNA sample if not already done and pay surcharge;
4) No contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent;
5) No possession of a smart phone;
6) No use of internet unless 1) for work or school; 2) be supervised by someone the agent deems appropriate; and 3) is approved by the agent.
7) Register all current and past internet accounts, user names and passwords with the DOC;
8) Spend ninety (90) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 01-20-16 by 6:00 p.m.;
9) Pay court costs;
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.   
Minutes.
